2015-08-19 <grm@melexis.com>     
    [*] \libsrc\products\81310\config\Extra.mk
        \libsrc\products\81315\config\Extra.mk
    Added defines for Loader protection to 81310 and 81315 products:
        #CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_HAS_PROTECTION_KEY                 # Loader protection mechanism enabling
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_PROTECTION_KEY_LENGTH=32            # key length can be whether 32 or 64 bits
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_PROTECTION_KEY_ADDR_FLASH=0xBF46    # protection key location into Flash
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_UNLOCKING_KEY_ADDR_NVRAM=0x1080     # unlocking key location into NVRAM

2015-08-19 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\products\81310\lib\
        \libsrc\products\81315\lib\
    Added 64-bit protection key section to 0xBF46 address for 81310 and 81315 products.

2015-08-19 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\products\81300\lib\
        \libsrc\products\81300\config\Extra.mk
    Added 64-bit protection key section to 0xBF46 address for 81300 product.
    Protection key address definition in Extra.mk was changed to 0xBF46:
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_PROTECTION_KEY_ADDR_FLASH=0xBF46    # protection key location into Flash

2015-08-19 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    LIN Loader: Added Loader protection with the key [PLTF-734]
    
    The LDR_HAS_PROTECTION_KEY is used to enable Loader protection mechanism 
    Protection key length (32 bits or 64 bits) is defined with LDR_PROTECTION_KEY_LENGTH=32/64.
    Also address of protection key into Flash is defined by LDR_PROTECTION_KEY_ADDR_FLASH
    and address of unlocking key into NVRAM is defined by LDR_UNLOCKING_KEY_ADDR_NVRAM.
    
    Application provides protection key which is hard coded to Flash.
    Also application reserves space into NVRAM area for unlocking key. 
    
    Loader is protected with key if the following two cases are true:
        1. If protection key’s high part is different from low part;
        2. If unlocking key in NVRAM is different from protection key.
    Otherwise, Loader isn’t protected with key, i.e. all commands available for executing.
    
    When Loader protected with key, the following commands can be executed only:
        - Enter programming mode
        - Read by identifier
        - Set Key
        - Restart
    Device will reply with ‘incorrect operation’ error if forbidden operation was required.    
    
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    LIN Loader: Added Set Key message implementation
    
    Set Key message sends unlocking key to the device enabling all Loader functions.
    Unlocking key will be written to allocated NVRAM area on address defined by LDR_UNLOCKING_KEY_ADDR_NVRAM.
    This massage is enabling with Loader protection mechanism (LDR_HAS_PROTECTION_KEY).
    
    [*] \libsrc\products\81300\config\Extra.mk
    Added defines for Loader protection:
        #CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_HAS_PROTECTION_KEY                 # Loader protection mechanism enabling
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_PROTECTION_KEY_LENGTH=32            # key length can be whether 32 or 64 bits
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_PROTECTION_KEY_ADDR_FLASH=0xBF40    # protection key location into Flash
        CPPFLAGS += -DLDR_UNLOCKING_KEY_ADDR_NVRAM=0x1080     # unlocking key location into NVRAM
        
    Loader protection mechanism is disabled. LDR_HAS_PROTECTION_KEY should be added to enable it. 
    
    [*] \libsrc\products\81300\lib\81300-lin.ld
                                  \81300-lin-loaderB.ld
    Space reserved for 64-bit protection key
    
2015-08-19 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
                   \flashupload.h
                   \lin.c
    LIN Loader: Renamed functions:
        - isEnterProgModeMessage() -> ldr_isEnterProgModeMessage;     
        - isReadByIdMessage()      -> ldr_isReadByIdMessage;
    
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    LIN Loader: Protocol Extension block was moved to the end of file.

2015-08-17 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\startup\sys_srv.S
    - mlx_enter_protected_mode function was changed: mov UPr, 0 was replaced with clrb MH.3. 
      This function cleans User bit only. Priority value is keeping unchanged. 
    
    [*] \include\syslib.h
    - Renamed ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE() to ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE_KEEP_PRIO() macros. 
      According to the changes into sys_srv.S, it enters system mode keeping priority register value;
    - Added ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE_PRIO_0() macros to enter system mode with zeroing of priority register value;
    - Added SYSTEM_CODE(__code__) macros to execute __code__ into system mode keeping priority register value.
    
    Note: ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE() macros is deprecated. 
          Please use ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE_KEEP_PRIO() or ENTER_SYSTEM_MODE_PRIO_0() instead.

2015-07-21 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
        \libsrc\LIN\lin.c
    LIN Loader: Added Read by identifier (ReadByID) message for LIN Loader [PLTF-673]

    When device into programming mode or Loader state is not equal to zero 
    then device answers to ReadByID message with the following identifiers:
      > Supplier ID (Melexis) = 0x0013
      > Function ID (Loader) = 0xCAFE
      > Loader state

2015-07-13 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \include\syslib.h
    Added emulated functionality to support __fsb() for mlx16 arch [PLTF-741]

2015-06-15 <pas@melexis.com>
    [*] \config\Config.mk updated to support utilities under the Linux OS

2015-06-11 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    LIN Loader: 
    - Added functionality to support flexible setting of Fast Protocol baudrate by communication messages [PLTF-672];
    - ML_FAST_BAUDRATE_K value is used as MAX baudrate value; Required baudrate will be saturated to ML_FAST_BAUDRATE_K;
    - ML_MIN_FAST_BAUDRATE_K value is used as MIN baudrate value.
    
    [+] \libsrc\LIN\ml_SetFastBaudRate.c
    LIN Loader: Added ml_SetFastBaudRate(baudrate) function to set custom baudrate for Fast Protocol on runtime.
    
    [*] \products\LINLoader\config_ini\MLXLIN_default
    Configuration file was updated as time to switch between Fast and LIN is increased
    - TFastToLin = 80000
    - TLinToFast = 80000
    
    [*] \products\813xx\config
    Changed LIN_APP profiles files: ML_FAST_BAUDRATE = 100000

