2015-02-17 <pas@melexis.com>
   [*] Flag SUPPORT_LINNETWORK_LOADER was moved from direct definition in \libsrc\LIN\flashfunctions_c_cmp.c and 
   \products\<PRODUCT>\src\premain.c to \products\<PRODUCT>\config\Extra.mk as CPPFLAGS += -DSUPPORT_LINNETWORK_LOADER for
   enabling functionality of storing LIN NAD into STACK_IT segment between resets of chip (This same address is used by LoaderB 
   premain). Functionlality was implemented and enabled in 81300, 81310, 81315, 81106/7/8/9 and 81150 projects. (PLTF-727)

2015-02-05 <pas@melexis.com> release 4.0.0.0 ---------------------------------
    Migration guide:
    ----------------
    To migrate application, that used LIN must chaged next points:
     - For starting LIN on fixed baudrate - must be executed command ml_SetDefaultBaudRate
       without any parameters or ml_SetBaudRate() with setting correct values of prescaller and divider.

     - For starting LIN on autobaudrate - must be executed command ml_SetAutoBaudRateMode() with parameter:
       ML_ABR_ON_FIRST_FRAME - for detecting baudrate on first frame and ML_ABR_ON_EACH_FRAME - on each frame.

     - function ml_ReleaseBuffer() not need to be executed from application. Must be removed.

     - For detectiong LIN_BUS_ACTIVITY_BIT, LIN_BUFFER_NOT_FREE_BIT or LIN_CMD_OVERFLOW_BIT must be executed command 
       ml_GetState() with parameter - which bit's will be cleared: ML_CLR_BUS_ACT_AND_OVF - bus activity and overflow,
       ML_CLR_LIN_CMD_OVERFLOW - overflow only, ML_CLR_LIN_BUS_ACTIVITY - only LIN bus activity, ML_NOT_CLEAR - nothing 
       to clear, and after that - read value of variable LinStatus with mask: ML_LIN_BUS_ACTIVITY, ML_LIN_BUFFER_NOT_FREE,
       ML_LIN_CMD_OVERFLOW.

      - Functions ml_SetOptions and ml_SetSlewRate was divided to separate functions.
        #if defined (HAS_LIN_SET_OPTIONS)
         ml_SetOptions(1U, 0U, ML_ENABLED, ML_LIGHTSLEEP);
         IDStopBitLength : 0 (default)/1/2/3 -> 1 / 1.5 / 2 / 2.5 stop bits
         TXStopBitLength : 0 (default)/1     -> 1 / 2 stop bits
         StateChangeSignal : enabled (default)/disabled
         * SleepMode: ML_LIGHTSLEEP or ML_DEEPSLEEP  
       #else
        Default options are used for LIN Module:
       - IDStopBitLength : 1 stop bits (code 0)
       - TXStopBitLength : 1 stop bit (code 0)
       - StateChangeSignal : enabled
       - SleepMode: lightsleep with timeout (ML_LIGHTSLEEP)
     
      SlewRate:
       ML_SLEWHIGH for baudrates above 15kbps
       ML_SLEWLOW  for baudrates below 15kbps
       ML_SLEWFAST for fast protocol mode
      ml_SetSlewRate(ML_SLEWLOW);

2015-02-05 <pas@melexis.com>
    [+] \products\LINLoader\config_ini\MLXLIN_default.ini
        Added ini-file of configuration for Melexis Programming Toolbox, which was used during the validation process.
        By default the settings will be saved in MLXLIN_default.ini file in the active user's directory. 
        E.g. "C:\Users\<user_name>\Application data\Melexis\MLXLIN\MLXLIN_default.ini"

2015-02-05 <pas@melexis.com>
    [*] \bin\ldf_nodegen.exe
        Updated to version 1.3.0
	- Supported changes in LIN API
	- Added switch to choose baudrate mode -b<d|f|e> (d: default baudrate from ldf-file,
          f: autobaudrate detection on first frame, e: autobaudrate detection on each frame)
        - Function mlu_AutoAddressingStep got attribute weak (PLTF-724)
        - Added callback for diagnostic messages with run-key -Sd (PLTF-712)

2015-02-05 <grm@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    LIN loader: Eliminated Loader ddErCFRAME error due to the permanent MLX4 evENDtx in Programming Mode
    
2015-01-20 <grm@melexis.com>
    [*] \include\mathlib.h
        \libsrc\math
        \products\Validation\MATHLIB\
    Integrated new version of MLX16 mathlib (2.4.0)
    - ASM realizations of some functions were replaced by INLINE_ASM 
    to optimize memory using and enhance calculation speed;
    - Flag '__MATHLIB_NON_INLINE__' forces ASM functions using,
    By default, INLINE_ASM is used

    [+] include\mathlib_inline.h
    [+] include\mathlib_non_inline.h
    Declaration of INLINE_ASM / ASM functionality

    [+] mul16_16by16_copr.S
        mul32_16by16_copr.S
        mulI16_I16byI16_copr.S
        mulI32_I16byI16_copr.S
    [*] mul16_16by16.S
        mul32_16by16.S
    Functions were splitted to different files to avoid linking with unused functions

