2014-11-20 <yso@melexis.com> patch release 3.3.4 -----------------------------
2014-11-20 <yso@melexis.com>
    [+] \libsrc\LIN\lin2b_v13_19200_12mhz.bin 
    lin2b_v13_19200_18mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_19200_20mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_19200_24mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_19200_25mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_19200_28mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_12mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_18mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_20mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_24mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_25mhz.bin
    lin2b_v13_9600_28mhz.bin 
    Restored LIN1.3 FW images which were removed in previous release

2014-11-20 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] vectors.S
    System exceptions (STACK_IT, PROT_ERR_IT, INV_AD_IT and PROG_ERR_IT)
    are now executed in USER mode (see request PLTF-718 on Jira)

2014-11-18 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.37
    3.1.35   : (2014-08-27)
        - Bug in erSTOP bit reporting corrected (PLTF-686)
        - Timeout when waiting for data ready if stop bit requested = 2 corrected (PLTF-685)
    3.1.36   : (2014-09-23)
        - Maximum header length treshold increased to 30 Tbits (PLTF-708)
        - bug in MSBI settings corrected when Mlx4 was receiving 3C-00 go to sleep request (PLTF-709)
    3.1.37   : (2014-11-12)
        - Bug corrected when collision during TX frame, next break was not measured correcly (PLTF-713)

2014-08-06 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] libsrc/LIN/flashfunctions_c_cmp.c
    Erase is performed two times in a row with (20ms each). See PLTF-700 request.

2014-08-05 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] \libsrc\Mlx4\Makefile
    Rearranged MLX4 assembler command line agruments to avoid
    error 'Superfluous Command-line text' with mlx16-gcc 1.12.3 toolchain

2014-04-30 <pas@melexis.com> patch release 3.3.1-----------------------------
2014-04-30 <pas@melexis.com>
    [*] Discarded removing the section with LIN Loader flags from the loaderB.hex
	for supporting programming chips, programmed with application, based on older
	version of SW platform. Jira PLTF-679
    [*] Changed \products\81300\include\nvram_mlx81300.h according to PLTF-678
    [*] Removed includes <string.h> and <stdbool.h> from LIN\flashfunctions_c_cmp.c

2014-04-16 <pas@melexis.com> release 3.3.0.0 ---------------------------------

2014-04-16 <yso@melexis.com>
    [+] \config\Rules.mk
    Added rules 'libs' and 'clean_libs' to build and clean profile's library.
    Variable $(PRODUCT) and $(PROFILE) are used to decide which profile should
    be build.
    Usage example:
    In the Makefile of the application, define $(PLTF_DIR) variable to
    relatively point to the root directory of the SW Platform:

    PLTF_DIR = ../../../..

    Now application can be build as:
    gmake libs all

2014-04-11 <pas@melexis.com>
    [+] Added new example for 81300 product:
	\products\81300\examples\LIN_Signal_layer_2_1

2014-04-04 <pas@melexis.com>
    [*] Updated \bin\ldf_nodegen.exe 
	according to PLTF-665 _AUTOADDtbl table in lin2b_romtbl.S is not empty now

    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashfunctions_c_cmp.c Flash_PageWriteFiltered (uint16_t addr)
	moved to __MLX_TEXT__ section.
	For validation this fix was updated ld-scripts in test examples:
	\products\81106_7\examples\IO_EX1_STANDALONE_LOADER\81106_7-fast-hi-flash-test.ld
	\products\81106_7\examples\LIN_EX1\81106_7-hi-flash-test.ld
	\products\81300\examples\IO_EX1_STANDALONE_LOADER\81300-fast-hi-flash-test.ld
	\products\81300\examples\LIN_EX1\81300-lin-hi-flash-test.ld

    [*] Changed \products\81300\include\nvram_mlx81300.h and
        \products\81300\include\ioports.h according to PLTF-666
     
    [*] Updated \products\81106_7\ and \products\81108_9\ according to PLTF-665

    [!] For APP_TYPE equal to LIN21_APP generated warning for using LIN20_APP
	and used the same MLX4 image.

    [!] Configuration LIN13_APP is not supported for this release

2014-03-14 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.34
           - MinprescA removed (PLTF-650)
           - LinBrcpt, Linbrhicpt carries removed (PLTF-641)
           - LinBrcpt size increased from 4 to 5 nibbles (PLTF-641)
           - LINprescA, LINbr, LINbrNom initialization added at startup
           - LINspclid is cleared at start of frame detection (PLTF-647)
           - Added LINpresc to be used with LINbr (PLTF-651)
           - Collision bit is cleared when starting break (PLTF-653)
           - Renamed LINstatus to LINerrStat
           - Changed from 1/2Tbit count to CPT count for zero bits
           - Frame flags and "data ready" cleared in case of an error
           - Header maximum length detection corrected (PLTF-644)

2014-03-13 <yso@melexis.com>
    [+] \LIN\ml_SetAutoBaudRateMode.c
    LIN: Added function to configure a mode of the LIN auto-baud rate.
    Three modes are defined. 
    1) ML_ABR_DISABLED: baud rate auto-detection is disabled and baud rate
      shall be configured by ml_SetBaudRate function
    2) ML_ABR_ON_EACH_FRAME baud rate is detected on each LIN frame
    3) ML_ABR_ON_FIRST_FRAME mode (default): baud rate is detected only
       once after calling this function

    Note: Direct changing of LinBaudCtrl is deprecated!


2014-03-03 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.33
    - Fixed baudrate code has been removed (fixed Br is handled by Auto baudrate code now) (PLTF-642)
    - Auto addressing is supported by auto baudrate code (PLTF-645)
    - Auto addressing bug is solved (AA uses LINbr instead of LINbrNom now) (PLTF-614)
    - Auto Baudrate support baudrates down to 1000 baud now (PLTF-641)

2014-02-28 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.32
    - Collision bug fixes for collision in ID and collision in data (PLTF-630)
    - Bug fix for collision in data when auto baudrate on every frame is enabled (PLTF-636)
    - Bug fix for RX uncomplete frame error report (PLTF-636)
    - Cleaned up error events, frame in frame handling and corresponding events

    Note: LIN auto-baudrate feature is enabled by default.

2014-01-27 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.28
    Different bug fixes and improvements to make the auto baudrate detection
    more robust for different break+delimiter combinations (PLTF-616)

2013-12-18 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] \bin\ldf_nodegen.exe
	Updated to version 1.2.0
	- Corrected for MISRA 2004 compliance
	- Added support for Frame Mode of LIN driver

2013-12-18 <yso@melexis.com> Implemented loader for H12 Flash

    WARNING! The H12 Loader requires the following versions of the PC-host components:
    - LIN Master firmware: 2.13 or above
    - MPT/LIN Master PSF:  1.39 or above
    - MPT/LIN Master UI:   1.27 or above
    
    The H12 loader also will work on H11 Flash by emulating sector erase
    via 16 page erases.

	[*] flashupload.c
	LIN Loader: Added Table #8 (implemented as _mlx_loader_info structure)
	to report to the host that loader supports dynamic programming delays 

	[*] flashupload.c
	LIN Loader: Optimized table operations: ddReadTable is an alias for
	ddReadAdd

	[*] flashupload_cfg.h
	LIN loader: Removed an obsolete table operations

    [*] \libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
    Loader optimization:
    - Optimized address base and offset calculations (removed ddDataAddressRq)
    - Optimized parsing of the command frame 
    - Optimized ddDataAddress and ddDataSize calculations
      
	[-] \libsrc\LIN\lin_state.c
	[+] \libsrc\LIN\loader_state.c 
		- Renamed lin_state.c to loader_state.c

	[*] libsrc\LIN\ml_InitLinModule.c
	libsrc\LIN\lin.c
	libsrc\LIN\flashupload.c
	- Replaced direct reading of the LoaderState by LDR_GetState().
	  Function LDR_GetState() calculates the loader state (0-3) based
	  on app_disabled, app_enabled and ldr_rst_vect_state_   

