2013-09-17 <pas@melexis.com>
    [*] bin\ldf_nodegen.exe
    bin\ncf_nodegen.exe
    Updated to version 1.0.0
    
    [*] Corrected generated driver for MISRA 2004 compliance (all deviation
        are documented)

2013-09-17 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    LIN: Updated MLX4 LIN FW to version 3.1.27
    - Rearranged the position of LINprescA variable to be at the fixed offset (+3 bytes)
    - Added option to execute LIN auto-baud rate procedure for each incoming
      frame [request PLTF-584]
    - Bug related to a shortcut (LIN bus = 0) is fixed [issue PLTF-600 on Jira]
    - Size optimization: ~150 bytes for Id-Filtering mode and ~40 bytes for
      Frame mode of the MLX4 LIN FW.
    - activated MLX4 option to reduce the size of MLX4 LIN tables
      (lin2b_romtbl.S), see coPARAMLT equ cvON
    - disabled next Frame Id feature (off HAS_LIN_NEXT_FRAME_ID)
    - format of the lin2b_romtbl.S tables has been changed;
      each entry in _PARAMtbl now takes 1 byte instead of 4 bytes;
      tables _FFiltTbl and _FLAGtbl have been removed
    - disabled functions ml_Receive, ml_Transmit and mlu_HeaderReceived in ID Filtering mode
    - disabled ml_EnableEndOfHeaderEvent, ml_DisableEndOfHeaderEvent
      (off HAS_LIN_DISCARDED_HEADER)
    - disabled ask API option is PARAMtbl
    - deprecated funcion mlu_HeaderReceived (not used in ID-Filtering mode of the LIN driver)
    - changed LIN API functions

        from [old]:
        extern void mlu_LinStateChanged(ml_LinState NewState, ml_LinState OldState, ml_StateReason Reason);
    
        to [new]:
        extern void mlu_LinSleepMode(ml_StateReason Reason);

    [*] libsrc\LIN\api.S
    libsrc\LIN\lin.h
    1. Changed type of LinProtectedID from ml_uint16 (word) to ml_uint8 (byte)
       for optimization and safety.
    2. Added LinBaudCtrl (ml_uint8) to control LIN autobaud-rate detection. 
    3. Moved bit ML_LIN_BAUDRATE_DETECTED from LinBusStatus to LinBaudCtrl.
    4. Added bit ML_LIN_AUTO_BAUD_ON_EACH_FRAME

    1) By default baud rate detection is enabled only once after reset, i.e.
    detection is executed on the Sync Field of the first received frame Header.

    2) To switch to permanent baud rate detection (on each frame) bit 0
    in variable LinBaudCtrl shall be set to 1 before a call to ml_Connect()
    in the application LIN initialization procedure.

    LinBaudCtrl |= ML_LIN_AUTO_BAUD_ON_EACH_FRAME;
    ml_Connect();

    3) To switch to the fixed baud rate the required baudrate shall be configured
    via ml_SetBaudRate function and then bit 1 in LinBaudCtrl shall be set to 1
    before a call to ml_Connect() in the application LIN initialization procedure.

    ml_SetBaudRate(prescaler, baud_counter);
    [...]
    LinBaudCtrl |= ML_LIN_BAUDRATE_DETECTED;
    ml_Connect();

    WARNING!! 
    Even in case of the auto-baud rate detection the initial baudrate shall be
    specified by calling ml_SetBaudRate function. This initial baudrate is
    used as a reference for a local wake-up sequence generation.
    If initial baud rate is not configured (by calling ml_SetBaudRate), the 
    local wake-up procedure (ml_WakeUp) might work incorrectly.

2013-09-11 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] libsrc\LIN_LoaderB\mlu30.c
    Changed state name from stSLEEP to ml_stSLEEP as per Melexis LIN API
    documentation

2013-09-11 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] bin\ldf_nodegen.exe
    bin\ncf_nodegen.exe
    Updated to version 0.9.0

	[*] Changed IsSupplierIdValid and IsFunctionIdValid to remove a warning
	of break strict-aliasing rules with getting value of current supplierId
	and functionID.
	
    [*] Changed conditonal compilation of ml_SetLoaderNAD based on
    HAS_SET_LOADER_NAD instead of LIN_PIN_LOADER

    [*] \products\<mulan2_products>\config\Extra.mk
    Added HAS_SET_LOADER_NAD definition

