	LIN: Added MLX4 LIN FW images for 12 MHZ and 24 MHz
	
2013-01-18 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] \libsrc\LIN\flashfunctions_c_cmp.c
	LIN: Added option (HAS_FLASH_WRITE_BUFFER_IN_NVRAM_SRAM) to allocate page write
	buffer in NVRAM SRAM area to save some general RAM. Size of the buffer is
	128 bytes and it is allocated at address 0x1100 (request PLTF-525)

    WARNING: When option HAS_FLASH_WRITE_BUFFER_IN_NVRAM_SRAM is enabled, loader
             uses NVRAM SRAM as a Flash Page buffer. That's why application
             should check that loader is not running before accessing the
             NVRAM SRAM. E.g. application can set a flag in mlu_ApplicationStop
             and then check if this flag is not set before accessing NVRAM or
             calling NVRAM functions like NVRAM_SavePage, NVRAM_SaveAll.
	
	[*] \libsrc\LIN\lin.c
	LIN: Optimized access to LinCommand

	[*] \include\mark.h
	Optmized mark macro-functions
	 	
2013-01-16 <yso@melexis.com> release 3.0.13.2 ---------------------------------
2013-01-16 <yso@melexis.com>
	[!] \libsrc\MUPET\mupet.h
	    \libsrc\MUPET\TEMPLATE\mupet_cbk.h
	MUPET: Integrated new version of MUPET SW module 0.2.1:  
	- Implemented workaround for MLXCOMP-17 issue (volatile access optimization)
	  during accessing PTC_STS port
	- Added extra check that EEPROM write is done only in PTC mode (bit PTC_MODE,
      see issue MLX16107-148)
	
2012-12-06 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] \include\lin.h
	LIN: Added ml_stINVALID state to ml_LinState (as per Melexis LIN API
	specification)

	[*] \libsrc\LIN\api.S
	\products\81300\config\Extra.mk
	LIN: Added timeout for MLX4 command acknowledgment (implementation
	is contributed by Marcel Braat). Option is configured by
	HAS_MLX4_CMD_ACK_TIMEOUT in Extra.mk and enabled by default
	for MLX81300. Timeout is defined as	MLX4_CMD_ACK_TIMEOUT in api.S

	[*] \libsrc\LIN\ml_InitLinModule.c
	LIN: If MLX4 doesn't acknowledge resynchronization with MLX16 within
	AWDG period, the MLX16 will be restarted by the watchdog.
	
