    Moved LinFrameDataBuffer[8] to dp section to reduce access time and
    optimize ROM space usage (PLTF-459)

2011-01-20 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] api.S, lin.c
	Removed IDdecode function and replaced it by direct LinID exctracting
	for optimization purposes
	
	[*] lin.c, lin.h
	[+] ml_InitLinModule.c, ml_LinInterruptHandler.c
	Splitted LIN event aknowledgement and LIN event processing in order to
	adapt the LIN driver for RTOS environment. Added functions
	ml_GetLinEventData and ml_ProccessLinEvent.  

2011-01-20 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] api.S
    Added conditional compilation (HAS_KEY_CHECK) for IsKey function (saved
    14 bytes)

2011-01-18 <yso@melexis.com>
    [+] Added RAM application profile

2011-01-18 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] Config.mk, Extra.mk
	Compiler switches -mwith-itc-bug-workaround and -mdpage-explicit are moved
    from common configuration file (Config.mk) to product specific
    configuration file (Extra.mk)
	
2011-01-18 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] Config.mk, Extra.mk
    Profiles are now included from Extra.mk after defining product specific
    settings. So, we have the following hierarchy now:
    Common settings -Product settings - Profile settings - Application settings
    The latest settings override previous ones. Thus Application settings could
    override profile and product settings.
    Removed EXTRA_DEF variable. All defines are assigned directly to CPPFLAGS.

2011-01-18 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] adclib.h
	Changed ADC_IS_BUSY function to use pending bit (CLR_ADC_IT) instead of
	checking ADC_EOC bit (see issue MMC16-42 for details). The second
	implementation based on analysis of both ADC_EOC and ADC_SOFT_TRIG can be
	used for MMC16 core >= 1.3

2010-12-28 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] Moved profiles (*.mk) from top level /config directory to the product
	directories: /products/$(PRODUCT)/config to improve product incapsulation
	(request PLTF-444 on Jira).
	NB!!! Now in order to build application variables PRODUCT and PROFILE must
	be specified either in command line or in application's Makefile  
	E.g.:
		gmake PRODUCT=<product_name> PROFILE=<profile_name> all
	
2010-12-02 <yso@melexis.com>
    [*] Linker scripts
    Removed loading data for Extra Page (.ep.data)

2010-11-09 <yso@melexis.com>
	[!] syslib.h 
	Changed name of local variable 'status' in ATOMIC_CODE to '_mreg_saved'
	This is to avoid possible conflict with reusing variable name in subscopes. 

2010-09-02 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] bin\ldf_nodegen.exe
    bin\ncf_nodegen.exe
    Updated to version 0.8se.9


2010-07-20 <yso@melexis.com>
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\lin2b.bin
    \libsrc\LIN\lin2b_v13_19200.bin
    \libsrc\LIN\lin2b_v13_9600.bin
    \libsrc\Mlx4\
    Updated LIN FW to version 2.6.49
    - frameIDs 0x3C and 0x3D could be preconfigured in MLX4 code.
      If MLX4 LIN FW is compiled with coSPECIALID cvON and
      coQR0_USED_BY_3D_FRAME equ cvOFF. Thus:
      1) 0x3C frame is assigned to message id 0x10 and confugured as
      master-to-slave, 8 bytes, classic checksum;
      2) 0x3D frame is assigned to message id 0x11 and configured as
      slave-to-master, 8 bytes, classic checksum;
      Values specified in LIN Confiruation tables (lin2b_romtbl.S)
      for 0x3c/0x3d frame IDs and 0x10/0x11 message indices have no effect
      Note that for current release this feature is disabled
      coSPECIALID is cvOFF and coQR0_USED_BY_3D_FRAME is cvOFF
    - fixed issue with watchdog reset after start bit error in TX mode (PLTF-485, PLTF-431)
	- erCRASH subcode set to 0 for attention interrupt (PLTF-485, PLTF-431)

2010-02-15 
    [!] \libsrc\LIN\ml_LinModuleVersion.c
    Corrected to accomodate to new address of mlx4_flash section


2010-01-12 <yso@melexis.com>
	[*] include\82050\uartlib.h
	Added new functions (see issue PLTF-410 on Jira)
		UART<n>_PUT_RAW -- to put raw unframed data to UART
	Set of functions to put frame data with start and stop bits:
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_7N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_8N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_9N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_10N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_11N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_12N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_13N1
		UART<n>_PUT_FRAME_14N1

	Function UART<n>_PUT is now deprecated.

